166,173,178,186,194,260,262,270,276,278,283,291,293,298,301,309,316,319,322],{"type":27,"text":55,"spans":56,"direction":24},"This post specifically addresses validator operators participating in the PoS migration. For general information on the migration, see this post: What You Need to Know About Nimiq's Migration to Proof of Stake.",[57,61],{"start":58,"end":59,"type":60},33,52,"strong",{"start":62,"end":63,"type":64,"data":65},145,209,"hyperlink",{"link_type":66,"url":67,"target":68},"Web","https://www.nimiq.com/blog/nimiq-is-migrating-to-proof-of-stake-what-you-need-to-know/","_blank",{"type":27,"text":70,"spans":71,"direction":24},"",[],{"type":27,"text":73,"spans":74,"direction":24},"You can find the full documentation here. Below is a short summary of the next steps for validator operators.",[75],{"start":76,"end":77,"type":64,"data":78},35,40,{"link_type":66,"url":79,"target":68},"https://www.nimiq.com/developers/migration/validator-activation",{"type":81,"text":82,"spans":83,"direction":24},"heading3","Steps for Validator Operators",[84],{"start":42,"end":85,"type":60},29,{"type":27,"text":87,"spans":88,"direction":24},"Main Prerequisite:",[89],{"start":42,"end":90,"type":60},18,{"type":92,"text":93,"spans":94,"direction":24},"list-item","Validator Registration: Your validator needs to be registered and appear on this list.",[95,97],{"start":42,"end":96,"type":60},22,{"start":98,"end":99,"type":64,"data":100},75,85,{"link_type":66,"url":101,"target":68},"https://nimiq.watch/#pre-staking",{"type":27,"text":103,"spans":104,"direction":24},"1. Join the Validator Operator's Chat",[105],{"start":42,"end":106,"type":60},37,{"type":92,"text":108,"spans":109,"direction":24},"Join Nimiq’s Discord or Telegram. Reach out to a Moderator/Team Member to verify yourself as a validator operator.",[110,115],{"start":111,"end":112,"type":64,"data":113},13,20,{"link_type":66,"url":114,"target":68},"https://discord.gg/nimiq",{"start":116,"end":117,"type":64,"data":118},24,32,{"link_type":66,"url":119,"target":68},"https://t.me/nimiq",{"type":27,"text":121,"spans":122,"direction":24},"2. Install the Latest PoW Release, now version 1.6.4, which was released on November 13, 2024.",[123],{"start":42,"end":124,"type":60},94,{"type":92,"text":126,"spans":127,"direction":24},"Download the code here or access compiled binaries here.",[128,132],{"start":129,"end":96,"type":64,"data":130},17,{"link_type":66,"url":131,"target":68},"https://github.com/nimiq/core-js/releases/tag/v1.6.4",{"start":133,"end":134,"type":64,"data":135},50,55,{"link_type":66,"url":136,"target":68},"https://www.nimiq.com/developers/build/nimiq-pow/downloads.html",{"type":92,"text":138,"spans":139,"direction":24},"Syncing Shortcut: Download a snapshot via IPFS or Torrent, extract it, and place it in your PoW client directory to speed up sync time. If using a third-party source, verify it with this SHA256 hash:",[140,142,147],{"start":42,"end":141,"type":60},16,{"start":143,"end":144,"type":64,"data":145},42,46,{"link_type":66,"url":146,"target":68},"https://ipfs.nimiq.io/ipfs/QmRKvFVpTdXagvgZG5cF9qdz13x9DkZhUvwXAS5YMaqTfu?filename=pow-main-full-consensus.zip",{"start":133,"end":148,"type":64,"data":149},57,{"link_type":66,"url":150,"target":68},"https://repo.nimiq.com/torrents/nimiq-pow-main-full-consensus.torrent",{"type":27,"text":70,"spans":152,"direction":24},[],{"type":27,"text":154,"spans":155,"direction":24},"\u003Ccode style=\"font-family: Fira Code; background: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.06);padding: 4px;border-radius: 4px;color: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.8);font-size: 0.8em;\">97fba2d6a9c8eaeb5fe568337e8052097fdffaae3f047b2f283e7007f30851cf  pow-main-full-consensus.zip\u003C/code>",[156],{"start":42,"end":157,"type":158,"data":159},252,"label",{"label":160},"HTML",{"type":27,"text":162,"spans":163,"direction":24},"3. Download the Latest PoS Release, now 1.0.0-rc.5, which was released on November 17, 2024.",[164],{"start":42,"end":165,"type":60},92,{"type":92,"text":167,"spans":168,"direction":24},"Download it here.",[169],{"start":170,"end":141,"type":64,"data":171},8,{"link_type":66,"url":172,"target":68},"https://github.com/nimiq/core-rs-albatross/releases/tag/v1.0.0-rc.5",{"type":27,"text":174,"spans":175,"direction":24},"4. Verify your Configuration",[176],{"start":42,"end":177,"type":60},28,{"type":92,"text":179,"spans":180,"direction":24},"Configure client.toml with your validator data as explained in Step 1 of the Activation Guide. ",[181],{"start":182,"end":183,"type":64,"data":184},63,93,{"link_type":66,"url":185,"target":68},"https://www.nimiq.com/developers/migration/validator-activation#step-1-add-validator-data-into-the-configuration-file",{"type":92,"text":187,"spans":188,"direction":24},"Verify that the seed list matches the list provided in the client.example.toml. The same list is provided below for confirmation:",[189],{"start":190,"end":191,"type":64,"data":192},59,78,{"link_type":66,"url":193,"target":68},"https://github.com/nimiq/core-rs-albatross/blob/albatross/lib/src/config/config_file/client.example.toml#L35C1-L51C2",{"type":27,"text":195,"spans":196,"direction":24},"\u003Cpre style=\"font-family: Fira Code; background: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.06);padding: 12px;border-radius: 4px;color: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.8);font-size: 0.8em;\">seed_nodes = [\n  { address = \"/dns4/aurora.seed.nimiq.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/catalyst.seed.nimiq.network/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/cipher.seed.nimiq-network.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/eclipse.seed.nimiq.cloud/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/lumina.seed.nimiq.systems/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/nebula.seed.nimiq.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/nexus.seed.nimiq.network/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/polaris.seed.nimiq-network.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/photon.seed.nimiq.cloud/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/pulsar.seed.nimiq.systems/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/quasar.seed.nimiq.com/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/solstice.seed.nimiq.network/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/vortex.seed.nimiq.cloud/tcp/443/wss\" },\n  { address = \"/dns4/zenith.seed.nimiq.systems/tcp/443/wss\" },\n]\u003C/pre>",[197,200,204,208,212,216,220,224,228,232,236,240,244,248,252,256],{"start":42,"end":198,"type":158,"data":199},166,{"label":160},{"start":201,"end":202,"type":158,"data":203},169,225,{"label":160},{"start":205,"end":206,"type":158,"data":207},228,290,{"label":160},{"start":209,"end":210,"type":158,"data":211},293,357,{"label":160},{"start":213,"end":214,"type":158,"data":215},360,419,{"label":160},{"start":217,"end":218,"type":158,"data":219},422,482,{"label":160},{"start":221,"end":222,"type":158,"data":223},485,541,{"label":160},{"start":225,"end":226,"type":158,"data":227},544,603,{"label":160},{"start":229,"end":230,"type":158,"data":231},606,671,{"label":160},{"start":233,"end":234,"type":158,"data":235},674,732,{"label":160},{"start":237,"end":238,"type":158,"data":239},735,795,{"label":160},{"start":241,"end":242,"type":158,"data":243},798,854,{"label":160},{"start":245,"end":246,"type":158,"data":247},857,919,{"label":160},{"start":249,"end":250,"type":158,"data":251},922,980,{"label":160},{"start":253,"end":254,"type":158,"data":255},983,1043,{"label":160},{"start":257,"end":258,"type":158,"data":259},1044,1051,{"label":160},{"type":27,"text":70,"spans":261,"direction":24},[],{"type":92,"text":263,"spans":264,"direction":24},"Verify the network configuration entry is set to main-albatross as provided in the client.example.toml. The final configuration should be the same one as below",[265],{"start":266,"end":267,"type":64,"data":268},83,102,{"link_type":66,"url":269,"target":68},"https://github.com/nimiq/core-rs-albatross/blob/albatross/lib/src/config/config_file/client.example.toml#L121",{"type":27,"text":271,"spans":272,"direction":24},"\u003Ccode style=\"font-family: Fira Code; background: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.06);padding: 4px;border-radius: 4px;color: rgba(31, 35, 72, 0.8);font-size: 0.8em;\">network = \"main-albatross\"\u003C/code>",[273],{"start":42,"end":274,"type":158,"data":275},185,{"label":160},{"type":27,"text":70,"spans":277,"direction":24},[],{"type":27,"text":279,"spans":280,"direction":24},"5. Compile the PoS Client",[281],{"start":42,"end":282,"type":60},25,{"type":92,"text":284,"spans":285,"direction":24},"Compile the PoS client as explained in Step 4 of the Activation Guide.",[286],{"start":287,"end":288,"type":64,"data":289},39,69,{"link_type":66,"url":290,"target":68},"https://www.nimiq.com/developers/migration/validator-activation#step-4-run-the-activation-tool",{"type":27,"text":70,"spans":292,"direction":24},[],{"type":27,"text":294,"spans":295,"direction":24},"6. Run the Activation Tool",[296],{"start":42,"end":297,"type":60},26,{"type":92,"text":299,"spans":300,"direction":24},"The activation tool will stay active until the end of the migration. It will signal “online” starting approximately 3 days before the candidate block at Proof of Work block #3’456’000. ",[],{"type":92,"text":302,"spans":303,"direction":24},"Once your validator “online” signal has been sent, it will appear as ONLINE on the Migration Readiness Monitor.",[304],{"start":305,"end":306,"type":64,"data":307},82,110,{"link_type":66,"url":308,"target":68},"https://nimiq-migration-monitor.netlify.app",{"type":92,"text":310,"spans":311,"direction":24},"When the Activation Phase opens and your validator produces a Genesis Hash, it will appear as READY on the Migration Readiness Monitor.",[312],{"start":313,"end":314,"type":64,"data":315},106,134,{"link_type":66,"url":308,"target":68},{"type":92,"text":317,"spans":318,"direction":24},"When more than 80% of the total stake has signaled readiness with the same Genesis Hash, the PoS chain will go live, and validators will begin producing blocks.",[],{"type":27,"text":320,"spans":321,"direction":24},"Remember to start this process as early as possible to ensure a smooth migration to Proof of Stake. Your dedication and support are invaluable in making this transition a success. Thank you for being an essential part of this journey. See you on the Proof of Stake Network!\n",[],{"type":27,"text":323,"spans":324,"direction":24},"Pura Vida\nTeam Nimiq",[325],{"start":42,"end":326,"type":60},9,"grey","rich_text$76ee4a41-ddd5-4810-b3fd-058cea84049e","rich_text",{},{"appsGroupName":332,"appsLinks":333,"howToTitle":490,"appsAdditionalFooterLinks":491,"howToLinks":492,"techGroupName":505,"techLinks":506,"githubLinkLabel":556,"techAdditionalFooterLinks":557,"techItems":558,"communityGroupName":573,"communityLinks":574,"communityItems":607,"communityAdditionalFooterLinks":617,"projectGroupName":620,"projectLinks":621,"projectAdditionalFooterLinks":665,"projectItems":666,"getStartedGroupName":679,"getStartedLinks":680,"newToCryptoTitle":38,"newToCryptoLinks":703,"getStartedAdditionalFooterLinks":704,"andMoreGroupName":705,"andMoreLinks":706,"legalPages":722,"extraHeaderLinks":723,"newsletterCta":724,"newsletterPlaceholder":725,"socialMediaCta":726,"nimiqShortDescription":727,"hothref":728,"hottext":736,"hotsince":737,"hotuntil":38,"announcementBannerHeadline":738,"announcementBannerCtaLabel":739,"announcementBannerCtaLink":740,"announcementBannerShow":18,"blocks":743,"copyrightNotice":870},"Apps",[334,367,386,416,438,464],{"logo":335,"visual":344,"label":353,"href":354,"link":365},{"dimensions":336,"alt":338,"copyright":38,"url":339,"id":340,"edit":341},{"width":337,"height":337},48,"Nimiq Logo","https://nimiq.cdn.prismic.io/nimiq/0dbc2a74-5cfb-4b19-a734-611379f6a591_nimiq-product-icon.svg","YlWuhRIAAC0AZFYp",{"x":42,"y":42,"zoom":342,"background":343},2,"#fff",{"dimensions":345,"alt":348,"copyright":38,"url":349,"id":350,"edit":351},{"width":346,"height":347},594,384,"Screenshot of the Nimiq Wallet","https://images.prismic.io/nimiq/18669675-be09-47fd-99bf-5c6eb8e091c0_header-wallet-hero.jpg?auto=compress,format&rect=0,0,